Example
Close a declare block:
<?php
$count = 0;
function example() {
global $count;
$count++;
echo "$count instructions executed<br>";
}
register_tick_function('example');
declare(ticks=1):
$cars = 
  ["Ford", "Volvo", "BMW"];
foreach($cars as $car) {
echo "$car <br>";
}
enddeclare;
?>

Definition and Usage
The
enddeclare
keyword is used to close a
declare
block which was started using the
declare(...):
syntax.
